partnerships have declined in value in  and  the  billion masterlimitedpartnership sector is the sausage maker of the investment world buyers love the yields — now averaging about  — but many know little about how the yields are generated the bullish pitch by brokers in favor of the investments centered around the highyielding way to participate in the booming us energy infrastructure buildout unfortunately the investments while providing generous yields masked the substantial high risks of these investments many of these investments were pitched to elderly and conservative investors because of the relatively high dividends and yields that the investments paid out these losses are potentially recoverable through either finra arbitration claims against the brokerage firms whose brokers recommended the investments or lawsuits against the promoters of the investments fraud based claims the second type of oil and gas actions deal with fraud based claims oil and gas investments take many forms including limited partnership interests master limited partnerships ownership of fractional undivided interests in leases and general partnerships risk level tax consequences and investor liability vary according to the type of program drilling partnerships have always been a gamble but unfortunately many oil and gas scams have been perpetrated by bad actors in the securities industry although some of the con artists moved on to more lucrative venues since the oil boom ended in the mids many continued to linger on in the oil field and the results of their actions are being felt now fraudulent oil and gas deals are frequently structured with the limited partnership or other legal entity in one state the operation and physical presence of the field in a second state and the offerings made to prospective investors in states other than the initial two states thus there is less chance of an investor dropping by a well site or a nonexistent company headquarters such a structure also makes it difficult for law enforcement officials and victims to identify and expose the fraud our securities law firm holds financial advisors accountable brokers at major brokerage firms like linsco lpl ubs merrill lynch raymond james citgroup and stifel nicolaus also sometimes engage in an activity called “selling away” when a broker sells a customer an “investment” outside the investment products offered by the brokerage firm and outside the client’s account there may be a selling away issue these investments known as private securities often involve investments in oil and gas related limited partnerships privately held companies private placements promissory notes and other similar investments sometimes they are real investments other times they are completely bogus and used as a means for the advisor to convert client funds unfortunately unscrupulous oil promoters and stockbrokers frequently use the internet and “boiler room” offices with banks of phones manned by salespeople with little or no background in energy exploration but plenty of experience in highpressure sales their techniques include repeated unsolicited phone calls to potential investors hyping the profitability of the deal and promises of safe but secure returns some examples of these pitches include • you will have an interest in a well that cannot miss • the risks are minimal • a geologist has given the salesperson a tip • the broker or salesperson has personally invested in the venture • the promoter has “hit” on every well drilled so far • there has been a tremendous “discovery” in an adjacent field • a large reputable oil company like chevron is operating or planning to operate in the area • only a few interests remain to be sold and you should immediately send in your money in order to assure the purchase of an interest • this is a special private deal open only to a lucky chosen few investors oil gas and energy deals we are investigating cushing royalty and income fund linn energy llc    parker drilling company  offshore group investment limited  midstates petroleum companytesoro petroleum co tso williams cos wmb kinder morgan kmi eog resources eog spectra energy corp se baker hughes inc bhi newfield exploration co nfx anadarko petroleum corp apc cimarex energy xec marathon petroleum mpc valero energy vlo schlumberger ltd slb conocophillips cop consol energy inc cnx exxon mobil corp xom national oilwell varco inc nov devon energy corp dvn phillips  psx chevron corp cvx eqt corporation eqt oneok oke occidental petroleum oxy fmc technologies inc fti hess corporation hes cameron international corp cam first solar inc fslr marathon oil corp mro helmerich  payne hp halliburton co hal cabot oil  gas cog southwestern energy swn murphy oil mur pioneer natural resources pxd apache corporation apa noble energy inc nbl chesapeake energy chk qep resources qep nabors industries ltd nbr diamond offshore drilling do range resources corp rrc ensco plc esv noble corp ne denbury resources inc dnr transocean rig if you lost money in oil gas or energy related investments please call our chicago based investment fraud law firm for a free evaluation by a lawyer as to whether those losses can be recovered through the finra arbitration process or through a lawsuit at  recent posts please call  today if you suffered forcefield energy fnrg losses and were recommended the investment by gerald cocuzzo and newbridge securities oil and gas recommendations with stephen swarbrick how to sue questar capital corp oil and gas investment losses because of joe zenker and raymond james losses with emerald oil how we can help for investors with noble royalty access funds berry petroleum company  wikipedia berry petroleum company from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search berry petroleum company type privately held company industry petroleum industry founded  headquarters denver colorado key people clarence berry founder products petroleum natural gas and natural gas liquids berry petroleum company is a petroleum natural gas and natural gas liquids exploration and production company based in denver colorado it was founded in  by clarence berry contents  current operations  history   oil spill  references  external links current operationsedit its operation areas include  in california  in the permian basin and  in the uintah basin historyedit berry petroleum company first started its exploration in  in california in august  berry petroleum agreed to buy tannehill oil and its affiliates for  million in  berry acquired properties in the uintah basin in northwestern utah in february  linn energy acquired berry petroleum company for  billion including  billion in stock in february  linn energy completed a financial restructure that included the corporate spinoff of berry into a separate company with separate ownership  oil spilledit in december  an oil pipeline owned by berry petroleum leaked resulting in a spill of  gallons of heavy crude oil into mcgrath lake near oxnard california berry had acquired the yearold pipeline from chevron in  after it had been abandoned for  years the line had been used to transport natural gas yet berry began to pump crude oil through it without making any upgrades moreover it was revealed that  months before the oil spill occurred a safety valve that might have prevented the leak had broken and was not repaired both berry and the state negotiated through the press with berry countering prosecutors threats with talk of suing the agencies that neglected to investigate witness reports and notify company officials of the leak several months later berry agreed to pay a  settlement and pleaded no contest to a single misdemeanor charge of failing to report the leak in addition the foreman on duty during the spill pleaded no contest to a charge of illegally releasing oil into marine water and was ordered to perform  hours of beach cleanup although free of criminal charges berry still faced a civil case from the state attorney generals office that matter was not to be settled until january  when the company agreed to a  million fine referencesedit  barry petroleum agrees to buy tannehill oil new york times august     berry petroleum buying uinta basin properties from williams oil  gas journal may     linn energy and linnco to acquire berry petroleum company for  billion press release globe newswire february     linn to buy berry petroleum for  billion to add oil reserves reuters february     linn energy successfully completes financial restructuring press release globe newswire february     us department of the interior berry petroleum co pipeline crude oil spill  jeff mcdonald august   berry petroleum pleads no contest in oil spill  penalty company ordered to pay  to settle criminal complaint over december pipeline rupture los angeles times   berry petroleum to pay  million oil spill penalty damages press release united states environmental protection agency january     california oil spill threatens small coastal wetlands area new york times december    external linksedit retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitleberrypetroleumcompanyoldid categories oil companies of the united statespetroleum in californiapetroleum in texascompanies based in denverenergy companies established in nonrenewable resource companies established in  establishments in california navigation menu personal tools not logged intalkcontributionscreate accountlog in namespaces article talk variants views read edit view history more search navigation main pagecontentsfeatured contentcurrent eventsrandom articledonate to wikipediawikipedia store interaction helpabout wikipediacommunity portalrecent changescontact page tools what links hererelated changesupload filespecial pagespermanent linkpage informationwikidata itemcite this page printexport create a bookdownload as pdfprintable version languages add links this page was last edited on  june  at  text is available under the creative commons attrib