 a fullservice upstream ep consultancy practice advising clients on ad strategic and operational initiatives and hillwood international energy an international ep company who had operations in the us russia and iraq while at hillwood trem oversaw strategic transactions representing over  billion of aggregate value and a  billion barrel resource discovery along with the associated  million development project prior to that trem spent  years in various roles at chevron corporation including president and general manager of russia operations where he led several major acquisition projects and operational initiatives trem graduated magna cum laude from amherst college with a major in geology and russian he has a masters and phd in economic geology from the pennsylvania state university cary baetz evp  chief financial officer mr baetz  has significant public company experience across the financial strategic planning and investor relations areas mr baetz most recently served as chief financial officer at seventy seven energy inc a domestic oil service company prior to that he served as senior vice president and chief financial officer of atrium companies inc a large private equity owned windows manufacturer prior to atrium mr baetz served as chief financial officer of boots  coots international well control an international well intervention and risk management company earlier in mr baetz’s career he served as vice president of finance treasurer and assistant secretary of chaparral steel company and director of corporate finance at texas industries inc mr baetz has led the sale of three public companies has successfully completed two public spinoffs and raised almost  billion in capital mr baetz holds a bachelor of science degree from oklahoma state university and a master of business administration degree from the university of arkansas gary grove chief operating officer mr grove has over  years of experience in the oil and gas industry bringing technical and executive m