 and risk management company earlier in mr baetz’s career he served as vice president of finance treasurer and assistant secretary of chaparral steel company and director of corporate finance at texas industries inc mr baetz has led the sale of three public companies has successfully completed two public spinoffs and raised almost  billion in capital mr baetz holds a bachelor of science degree from oklahoma state university and a master of business administration degree from the university of arkansas culture berry’s culture is reminiscent of a time when it wasn’t unusual for employees to work their whole life for one company one where trust honesty and fair dealing are a way of life it’s a culture of balance that recognizes the need for productivity creativity and downtime away from work the company fosters an entrepreneurial spirit and encourages its teams to apply improvements at every level moving the company forward berry’s employees belong to the communities where they work so the company’s interests are aligned with those who live near operations berry expects to have a positive presence in the communities surrounding its operations history berry petroleum’s roots reach back to  through its predecessor companies founded by cj berry but today’s company is a new and different berry with new ownership and management more than  years ago a man named cj berry armed with determination and not much else set out on a journey to seek his fortune that path would lead from the gold claims of the klondike to the oil fields of central california his success was manifold and one lasting result is berry petroleum company a californiabased energy company that began when cj began producing heavy oil from the san joaquin basin in  settling on a piece of land in the southern san joaquin valley nestled up against the temblor range cj began to drill for oil he started many oil companies as early as  with names like bakersfield fuel oil el dorado oil company and mammoth oil company one of his early wells was drilled on some land named for his wife ethel d in  some  plus years later the ethel d property is still producing oil in paying quantities berry holding company formed in  as one of cj’s many companies continued to grow over the years and in december  was merged with several related entities into berry petroleum company berry with a very solid beginning has continued to grow and evolve and today is one of the few remaining independent producers headquartered in california berry expanded its presence in areas outside of california beginning in  as opportunities to acquire light oil and natural gas became available to grow its portfolio today berry has production in five states and is always looking for acquisitions to continue the course of success and growth that cj envisioned when he drilled his first well on the ethel d lease linn energy and linnco acquired berry in  and subsequently linn filed for bankruptcy in may  berry emerged from the bankruptcy as a standalone company on feb   berry petroleum company llc is now an independent whollyowned subsidiary of berry petroleum corporation cj and ethel d berry go to top   oil and gas operational areas  berry petroleum company llc skip to content search   berry petroleum company llc berry petroleum company llc linkedin home about berry operations corp responsibilitycommunity investors contact legal notice operational areas berry is an independent privatelyheld energy company engaged in the acquisition exploration development and production of oil and natural gas reserves currently focused in the san joaquin basin in california the uinta basin in utah the piceance basin in colorado the hugoton basin in kansas and the east texas basin in east texas california  net acres   san joaquin and east ventura basins — the california region consists of oil and gas properties located in the midwaysunset mckittrick poso creek and south belridge fields in the san joaquin valley basin as well as the placerita field in the e ventura basin the properties in the midwaysunset mckittrick placerita poso creek and south belridge fields produce using thermal enhanced oil recovery methods at depths ranging from  feet to  feet thermal production in the san joaquin valley basin is primarily from the tulare potter monarch and diatomite formations and in the e ventura basin thermal production is from the upper and lower kraft formations the company’s properties in this region are primarily mature lowdecline oil wells colorado  net acres   piceance basin — the colorado assets consist of gas producing properties located in the piceance basin of western colorado the properties are produced from a basincentered gas play at depths ranging from  feet to  feet wells are hydraulically fractured and produce dry gas from williams fork formation with plunger lift operations the company’s properties in this region are primarily mature lowdecline gas wells utah  net acres   uinta basin — the utah assets consist of oil and associated gas producing properties located in the uinta basin of northeastern utah the properties produce  api gravity oil at depths ranging from  feet to  feet wells are hydraulically fractured and produced with conventional lift methods on primary production from the wasatch and green river formations ngls are recovered through a companyowned and operated facility the company’s properties in this region are primarily mature lowdecline oil wells kansas  net acres   hugoton basin — the hugoton basin is a large oil and natural gas producing area located in southwest kansas the company’s nonoperated kansas properties primarily produce from the council grove and chase formations at depths ranging from  feet to  the company’s properties in this region are primarily mature lowdecline natural gas wells texas  net acres   east texas basin — the east texas basin has an extensive basincentered overpressured gas cell on the west flank of the east texas basin berry’s assets consist of properties located in harrison and limestone counties and primarily produces natural gas from the cotton valley taylor and bossier sand formations at depths ranging from  feet to  feet go to top berry petroleum company llc private company information  bloomberg july    pm et oil gas and consumable fuels company overview of berry petroleum company llc snapshot people company overview berry petroleum company llc engages in the production and development of oil and natural gas in the united states the company holds properties located in san joaquin valley and los angeles basins in california hugoton basin in kansas and the oklahoma panhandle uinta basin in utah and piceance basin in colorado and east texas it sells oil and natural gas to various customers including pipelines refineries and other oil and natural gas companies as of december   the company had proved reserves of approximately  million barrels of oil equivalent it also generates and sells electricity to utility companies the company was founded in  and is headquartered in houston te berry petroleum company llc engages in the production and development of oil and natural gas in the united states the company holds properties located in san joaquin valley and los angeles basins in california hugoton basin in kansas and the oklahoma panhandle uinta basin in utah and piceance basin in colorado and east texas it sells oil and natural gas to various customers including pipelines refineries and other oil and natural gas companies as of december   the company had proved reserves of approximately  million barrels of oil equivalent it also generates and sells electricity to utility companies the company was founded in  and is headquartered in houston texas energy llc detailed description  travissuite houston tx united statesfounded in  phone  key executives for berry petroleum company llc mr mark e ellis chief executive officer and president age  mr david b rottino chief financial officer and executive vice presiden